' Sound surface smoke. Exercises the full command path end to end —
' LoadSound -> PlaySound -> StopSound -> SoundPlaying -> DeleteSound — through the
' opaque Sound / SoundChannel types and the PlaySound statement form.
'
' The assertions are DEVICE-INDEPENDENT: the audible behaviour needs a real
' output device and is verified separately (deferred smoke). On a host with audio
' LoadSound/PlaySound succeed and StopSound makes the channel stop; on an
' audio-less host they degrade to Null and the null-Sound trap is suppressed — so
' SoundPlaying after StopSound is 0 either way, and the program runs identically.

' Preloaded sample, played as a one-shot, then stopped.
Dim s As Sound = LoadSound("beep.wav")
Dim ch As SoundChannel = PlaySound(s)
StopSound ch
Print "stopped=" + Str(SoundPlaying(ch))

' SetSound on the (now stopped/finished) channel is a safe no-op.
SetSound ch, 1
Print "after_set=" + Str(SoundPlaying(ch))

' PlaySound as a fire-and-forget statement (the returned channel is discarded),
' plus the streamed filename form. Both degrade to a non-playing channel without
' audio; neither is asserted on directly.
PlaySound s
Dim music As SoundChannel = PlaySound("beep.wav")
StopSound music
Print "music=" + Str(SoundPlaying(music))

DeleteSound s
Print "done"
